CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Academic/Career
DESCRIPTION:Join the Weather Club and the Indiana AMS Chapter for a collab
 orative meeting featuring National Weather Service Indianapolis staff and
  a behind-the-scenes look at the May 16th tornado event. Forecasters who 
 worked the storm in real time will walk us through radar analysis\, warni
 ng decisions\, and operational challenges during the event.\nParticipants
  will engage in interactive activities\, including map and radar analysis
 \, to explore how meteorologists interpret data and issue life-saving war
 nings. This is a great opportunity to connect with NWS professionals\, le
 arn about severe weather operations\, and gain hands-on forecasting exper
 ience.\n\nHosted by: Student American Meteorological Society Chapter at I
 ndiana University\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://bein
 volved.indiana.edu/event/12217178
DTEND:20260310T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260309T220000Z
LOCATION:Ballentine Hall\, BH 206
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CANCELLED
SUMMARY:Indiana AMS & Weather Club Joint Meeting: NWS Case Study Night
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12217178
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12217178
X-HOSTS:Student American Meteorological Society Chapter at Indiana Univers
 ity
