CATEGORIES:Sexual Violence Prevention
CATEGORIES:Engage & Thrive - Community
DESCRIPTION:\nThe It’s On Us: Bystander Intervention Workshop is a 90-minu
 te\, audience-driven bystander intervention program that teaches students
  the skills needed to help in situations involving alcohol and drug use t
 hat could lead to a sexual assault. Students practice helping in real-lif
 e scenarios and discuss how alcohol and drug use influences a person’s ab
 ility to give and get consent to engage in sexual activity with another p
 erson.  \n\n\nIt's On Us is required for all first-year and transfer unde
 rgraduate students. You must attend one session to fulfill the requiremen
 t.  \n\n\nInstructions:  \n\n\nThose who arrive more than 5 minutes after
  the start time will NOT be allowed into the session and will need to att
 end a different session \n\n\nIf this is your assigned workshop but you c
 annot attend it in its entirety\, please RSVP for a different workshop. \
 n\n\nAll Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, educational\, 
 cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other m
 embers of the Indiana University community. \n\n\nHosted by: Office for S
 exual Violence Prevention and Victim Advocacy\n\nAdditional Information c
 an be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11970648
DTEND:20260311T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260310T220000Z
