DESCRIPTION:The Pi Day Math Challenge is an interactive\, team-based compe
 tition designed to celebrate mathematics in a fun and engaging way. The e
 vent will feature three rounds of Jeopardy-style gameplay\, with each rou
 nd increasing in difficulty. Participants will work together to solve mat
 h problems spanning logic\, problem-solving\, computation\, and creative 
 thinking. A special highlight of the event is a featured team of Purdue s
 tudents\, who attendees will compete against in a friendly but spirited s
 howdown. The Jeopardy rounds will also include a unique twist\, adding an
  unexpected and exciting element to the traditional format.All attendees 
 will receive a free pie in celebration of Pi Day\, and the winning team w
 ill receive a special prize. Whether you're a math enthusiast or just in 
 it for the pie\, this event promises an evening of challenge\, collaborat
 ion\, and fun. Be there or be squared!\nAll Indiana University events\, g
 roups\, activities\, and educational\, cultural\, and historical observan
 ces welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana University c
 ommunity.\n\nHosted by: Indiana Memorial Union Board\, Mathematics Club a
 t IU\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indian
 a.edu/event/12310428
