DESCRIPTION: \nThe Turkish Student Association at Indiana University is or
 ganizing a Çanakkale Martyrs’ Commemoration and Ramadan Iftar Gathering o
 n March 18. This event aims to honor the historical significance of the G
 allipoli Campaign (1915)\, a pivotal moment in World War I that carries d
 eep meaning not only for Türkiye but also for many nations around the wor
 ld.\nÇanakkale represents stories of sacrifice\, resilience\, and humanit
 y that transcend national boundaries. The campaign involved soldiers from
  different countries\, and over time it has become a symbol of remembranc
 e\, mutual respect\, and reconciliation. Through this commemoration\, we 
 aim to reflect on these shared historical narratives and promote intercul
 tural understanding within the IU community.\nIn addition to the commemor
 ation\, we will host an iftar dinner\, marking the breaking of the fast d
 uring the holy month of Ramadan. Iftar is a time of reflection\, gratitud
 e\, and community\, and we welcome students\, faculty\, and community mem
 bers of all backgrounds to share this meaningful cultural tradition toget
 her.\n\nHosted by: Turkish Student Association at Indiana University\n\nA
 dditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/eve
 nt/12302054
DTEND:20260319T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260318T230000Z
LOCATION:IMU Frangipani Room
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
