DESCRIPTION:For this workshop\, the common myth of productivity and self-e
 fficacy will be discussed to help attendees find out how to feel good abo
 ut their work and projects. Plus\, there will be a discussion (or self-di
 scussion) about finding their own definition of rest and rejuvenation. Hy
 e Ree earned her Doctor of Psychology (Psy.D.) degree in Clinical Psychol
 ogy with a focus on traumatic stress psychology from Adler University in 
 Chicago. Hye Ree serves as an embedded counselor at the ACC. \nAll Indian
 a University events\, groups\, activities\, and educational\, cultural\, 
 and historical observances welcome all IU students and other members of t
 he Indiana University community.\n\nHosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nAd
 ditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/even
 t/12168296
