BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Call-Out Meeting
CATEGORIES:Arts & Humanities
CATEGORIES:Engage & Thrive - Community
CATEGORIES:Campus-Wide Event
DESCRIPTION:What does it mean to be an "other"? How can writing shift the 
 boundaries between insider and outsider for both author and audience? All
  are welcome to join the ACC in discussing these questions over dinner th
 rough Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay collection To Save and to Destroy: Writin
 g as an Other. Originally delivered as the Norton Lecture series at Harva
 rd in 2023-24\, the six chapters span Nguyen's reflections on war\, solid
 arity\, and power\, drawing from sources ranging from classics of America
 n literature to Nguyen's own lived experience as a refugee. Digital copie
 s of the eBook are freely available to access through IU Libraries\, so a
 ll attendees are welcome to read ahead! Pizza will be served at each meet
 ing. \nFor more information\, please reach out to ACC volunteer and book 
