CATEGORIES:Speaker
CATEGORIES:Academic/Career
DESCRIPTION:Katherine Hibbs Pherson\, Chief Executive Officer of Globalyti
 ca and the VEXAS Global Foundation\, teaches advanced analytic techniques
  and critical thinking skills to analysts in government\, academia\, and 
 the private sector and consults to the government on planning\, security\
 , and analysis projects. She and the late Randy Pherson are co-authors of
  Critical Thinking for Strategic Intelligence\, 3rd ed. (2021). Ms. Phers
 on currently serves as the Vice President of the International Associatio
 n for Intelligence Education (IAFIE). As the past vice chair of the Intel
 ligence and National Security Alliance’s (INSA) Security Policy Reform Co
 uncil (2010-2024)\, she served as INSA’s representative to the National I
 ndustrial Security Program Policy Advisory Committee (NISPPAC). She has s
 ince 2018 supported the US Government’s Trusted Workforce 2.0 (TW 2.0) tr
 ansformation initiative. Ms. Pherson in 2000 completed a 27-year career w
 ith CIA in intelligence and security analysis and resource management. He
 r leadership in security led to the adoption of a risk management methodo
 logy\, strengthening and implementation of overseas security countermeasu
 res\, and improvements in dealing with unsolicited contacts.\n\nHosted by
 : Intelligence and Security Club\n\nAdditional Information can be found a
 t: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11981959
DTEND:20260327T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260327T170000Z
LOCATION:BLGA 1122 - Global & International Studies Building
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Kathy Pherson Speaker Event
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11981959
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11981959
X-HOSTS:Intelligence and Security Club
END:VEVENT
