DESCRIPTION:<!--StartFragment -->\nThe History Graduate Student Associatio
 n (HGSA) at Indiana University is organizing the annual Paul Lucas Gradua
 te History Conference on Friday and Saturday\, April 3 and April 4\, 2026
 . This interdisciplinary conference is inspired by the manifold questions
  raised by the notion of “crisis.” We welcome submissions for individual 
 papers from graduate students of all disciplines\, including\, but not li
 mited to\, History\, Anthropology\, Political Science\, Sociology\, Geogr
 aphy\, Art History & Literature\, Religious Studies\, Area Studies\, Cult
 ural Studies\, Gender Studies\, and Queer Studies. Proposals may include 
 any temporal\, thematic\, and geographic approaches to historical inquiry
 . \n<!--EndFragment -->\n\nHosted by: History Graduate Student Associatio
 n\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.e
 du/event/11981599
DTEND:20260404T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260403T120000Z
LOCATION:IMU Dogwood Room April 3rd & IMU Walnut Room April 4th
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Paul Lucas Graduate History Conference
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11981599
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11981599
X-HOSTS:History Graduate Student Association
END:VEVENT
