DESCRIPTION:Rubber Duck Race! All funds will be distributed equally among 
 two local humane societies and the Mu Chapter of APO. These organizations
  are dedicated to supporting animal welfare in Brown and Monroe Country. 
 For every dollar\, purchase one duck to be raced at during the Rubber Duc
 k Race!\nAt the race\, we will hear from local organizations addressing a
 nimal welfare with IU student organizations\, play lawn games\, do fun ac
 tivities\, buy merch\, and of course\, race ducks! This event is open and
  free to all!\nThe Mu Chapter of Alpha Phi Omega at Indiana University ha
 s had a long tradition of conducting a spring service project that gives 
 back to our community and develops these pillars in our chapter and campu
 s. Alpha Phi Omega is a national co-ed service fraternity dedicated to th
 e pillars of leadership\, friendship\, and service. In the spring\, we ho
 ld an event called the Rubber Duck Race. At this race\, donors can purcha
 se a rubber duck for one dollar to be thrown into the Campus River by the
  Indiana Memorial Union. We additionally have food and tables for local s
 tudent and community organizations to do outreach.\nIn 2025\, all funds r
 aised will go directly to supporting efforts to reduce food insecurity in
  Monroe County. Specifically to two local organizations\; Brown County Hu
 mane Society and Monroe County Humane Association. We are hoping that by 
 opening the opportunity to the larger IU and Bloomington community\, we c
 an engage citizens and students in the cause of food insecurity. Join us 
 in supporting the local Bloomington and IU community with a donation toda
 y!\n\nHosted by: Alpha Phi Omega\n\nAdditional Information can be found a
 t: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12282148
DTEND:20260411T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260411T170000Z
LOCATION:Dunn Meadow 2 (East side)
