DESCRIPTION:The Asian Culture Center In collaboration with the City of Blo
 omington Community and Family Resources Department presents 2026 Asianfes
 t\, an annual campus-community partnership featuring cultural and informa
 tion tables\, performances\, and video clips/slides about Asian American 
 and Pacific Islander heritage.\n \nMosaic Traditions: Piecing a Common Gr
 ound highlights the enduring legacy of asian art forms evolving through g
 enerations. \n \nThe tales we tell and the stories we share all bear our 
 past\, present\, and future—across time and space.  And thus\, we meet to
 gether\, where cuisines merge in fusion\, attire becomes fashion\, music 
 becomes memories\, and trends become traditions. \n \nWe all possess both
  ancestral wisdom and foresight that converge in the present\, reminding 
 us to learn from the past while remaining prudent in facing the future.  
 \n \nWelcome to AsianFest 2026\, where we celebrate our shared histories 
 and unique heritages. Through this year’s theme\, Mosaic Traditions: Piec
 ing a Common Ground\, we invite one and all to find peace on common groun
 d. \n \nAll Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, and educati
 onal\, cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and 
 other members of the Indiana University community.\n\nHosted by: Asian Cu
 lture Center\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolve
 d.indiana.edu/event/12011874
