DESCRIPTION:Union Board\, in collaboration with the IU Arts and Humanities
  Council\, is excited to announce a Conversation with Caleb Hearon as par
 t of the yearly Granfalloon festival.\nPurchase a ticket through this lin
 k:https://www.iuauditorium.com/events/detail/calebhearon-2026 \nStudents 
 can reserve up to one free ticket. \nCaleb Hearon is a comedian\, writer\
 , and actor known for his clever humor and commentary. He is the host of 
 the popular podcast So True with Caleb Hearon\, where he combines persona
 l storytelling with comedic insight\, and he has built a national reputat
 ion through stand-up performances\, television writing\, and live shows.\
 nOriginally from the Midwest\, Hearon began performing comedy at a young 
 age and has since appeared at major comedy festivals while touring extens
 ively across the United States. He also recently came out with his first 
 HBO comedy special\, which is deeply personal and comments on identity\, 
 grief\, and growing up queer in the Midwest.\nThis event will be in partn
 ership with the IU Arts and Humanities Council to kick off and promote Gr
 anfalloon 2025: \nPresented by the IU Arts and Humanities Council and ins
 pired by legendary Hoosier author Kurt Vonnegut Jr.\, Granfalloon brings 
 together musicians\, artists\, thinkers\, and good people from all walks 
 of life for a celebration of art\, ideas\, and community.\nThe festival h
 ighlights the creative spirit of our region by tapping into the enduring 
 ethos of Vonnegut’s life and work: promoting civic engagement\, encouragi
 ng independent thought\, and championing art and creativity as essential 
 to the spiritual life of individuals and the health of our democracy.\n\n
 Hosted by: Indiana Memorial Union Board\n\nAdditional Information can be 
 found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12145323
DTEND:20260415T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
